Hi everyone,

Yandex is looking for an experienced Data Analyst/Data Scientist to hold webinars and record educational videos on *Practicum by Yandex*, our educational platform. Practicum offers intensive 10-month career advancement programs in tech. As a tutor you will assist students throughout the educational process by answering questions, helping with any difficulties, sharing your experience and giving them practical advice through video webinars and Slack chats. You will have a group of ~30-50 students.

*We appreciate it if you:*
• Can explain topics in Python, Python libraries, SQL, statistics, mathematics, machine learning, data visualization tools in a way that students will understand;
• Know how to perform a/b testing;
• Highly proficient in spoken and written English;
• Ready to dedicate at least seven hours a week to this project;
• Some educational content video recordings (on YouTube or other platforms) is a plus;
• Teaching or tutoring experience is a plus.
*I’m a good fit. What can you offer me?*
• $40-50/hr for tutoring one group of students (the compensation is adjust for your skill level);
• Remote, part-time job 3-4 hours per week;
• Free training for tutors;
• Cross-cultural work experience in tutoring and giving webinars;
• An opportunity to become a part of an international community of developers.
If you feel like you might be a good fit please drop us a message at <mailto:ilinovamarian@yandex-team.ru|ilinovamarian@yandex-team.ru>
